      <section eId="sec_227_340">
        <num>227.340</num>
        <content>
          <p>Whenever the state fire marshal, his deputy, or other officer has reason to believe that a fire hazard should be corrected and he is unable to determine after a diligent search the owner of any property to be affected, he shall, in addition to notice required in KRS , post notice of a hearing concerning the hazard in a conspicuous place on or near the property and shall also publish notice pursuant to KRS  in the county in which the property is located. The hearing shall be held in accordance with KRS  at the time and place specified in the notice as if the notice had been served on the owner.</p>
        </content>
